cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper deals with attention mechanisms in convolutional neural networks for image classification and fine-grained recognition, which are topics commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) research. Additionally, the use of attention mechanisms can also be relevant in natural language processing (cs.CL), as they can be used to selectively focus on certain parts of text.
